element.name: E is for Electron by Hezekiah, Traditional Cache (1/1)

center.font: Visit the new Geocaching Ireland discussion forum HERE

element.long-description: The man who first coined the term "electron" (in 1891)is buried here - George Stoney. A nearby road is named after him- Stoney Road, surprisingly enough! There is another Stoney Road in the North side of Dublin, named after his brother, who was a famous engineer and pioneered a new method of building piers and harbour walls, notably the North Wall in Dublin.
